Engaging mini-games test your reading, writing and speaking skills, and joining a club (where you can encourage and compete with others) adds a great social element. Bonus: all those languages and games are available for free!

Deciding what to serve and whether to bake, boil, fry, chop, puree, or season it—or all of the above—will keep young chefs happily cooking away.
